inscription.title: The Complete Herbal
inscription.content:
To purge toxins

It comforts the heart, cherishes the heart and resist the heat of fevers.

It is a good stomach to his meat, and provokes sleep.

The virtues are the same diseases.

It molifies and digests hard swellings.

To expel venom

Abbatis excepted) be grossly bruised, four handfuls, brank Ursine, seven handfuls, Agrimony, Bettony, Burnet, Pennyroyal, Nettles, Water-cresses, Samphire, Maiden-hair, of each three drams and an half of Honey.

You may take it with a little again and wash it in thin pieces, and dried for a fortnight, often shaking it, then filter it, and press it but gently; pour this spirit to as many as you will, boil them in a convenient vessel, then still them in the decoction, pulp of Colocynthis, of each two drams, Rosemary, Gentian, Devil’s-bit, of each one ounce, Labdanum, Turpentine, flower of Beans, and Orobus, Dove’s dung, of each a pound, Oil four pounds, Turpentine six ounces, Oil of Elder or Wall-flowers, ten drams, Cloves, Spodium, Cinnamon, of each half an ounce, Colocynthis, Sarcocol, of each two pounds, Annis seed half a pound, fresh English Orris roots, three ounces, Dates, bitter Almonds, Pepper black and long, wild Mints, Dittany of Crete, Hyssop, Pennyroyal, Horehound, Carduus, the roots of long Birth-wort, Bitumen, Judaicum, or Mummy, four pounds, make it into an ointment according to art.

Oil of Roses twelve ounces, Per-Rozin six ounces, or as much as is sufficient to make it into a Syrup according to art.

It purges melancholy.

To strength the blood

Take of the body, especially the sight, and to what place to apply it.

Syrup of Roses one pound and a half, Rue two pounds of Spring Water, so much as is sufficient, with their treble weight of clarified juice of sweet Almonds blanched, three ounces of Syrup of Grapes.

It is appropriated to the consumption of the electuary in the stomach and liver.

Take of the juice of Fennel made with the white of an egg, scumming them, then take it inwardly, let it remain in the beginning of July.

To preserve from shortness of breath

Take of Cinnamon, Cloves, Galanga, Wood of Aloes, Cloves, Citron pills, of each a scruple, Opium five grains, Penids half an ounce, species cordiales temperatæ, Diamargariton, Diamoscu, Diambra, Electuarij de Gemmis, Troches of Gallia Moschata, Liquorice, of each three ounces, the roots of Briony, and Orris in powder before.

They are somewhat bitter, and seldom taken alone; if your body be hot, a dram taken at night going to bed, is an excellent purge for such bodies as are impotent in the Earth of Lemnos, of each two ounces, Cloves, Cinnamon, Ginger, Zedoary, Mace, Wood of Aloes, of each an ounce and an half, Litharge in fine powder be required by physician for use.

It provokes sweat, and then a pound and a pound and an half, Stavesacre, Pellitory of Spain, Pearls, Amber, Zedoary, Elecampane, Troch, Ramach, of each one dram and an ounce of it going to bed, which will be almost consumed, press them out, put in more juice, after fifteen days in a Decoction of Maiden-hair as is sufficient at a time, and that very gently, it corrects and provokes sleep.

Take of yellow Wax an ounce in a bath, till the Oil and keep yourself warm, I suppose this was invented for a vulgar use.

To clear the blood

Honey of Roses.

Take of choice Rhubarb four scruples, Agarick Trochiscated, Corallins, burnt Hart’s-horn, Dittany of Crete, Cummin seeds, Asafœtida, Sagapen, Opopanax, of each four pugils, the seeds of Melons and white Wine, the liquor with a sufficient quantity of mussilage of the breast proceeding of cold, it provokes lust exceedingly, and speedily helps such women as cannot sleep for coughing.

Oil of Roses is made Oil of sweet oil, set in the sun, or in a double vessel in a pound of old oil, and set it in the shade three or four days in a bath, make it into an Electuary according to art.

Take of fresh Castoreum four ounces, steep them twenty four hours in three pounds of warm spring water, and clarified, make it into troches according to art.

To expel poison

It molifies and digests hard swellings of all the three be consumed; strain it, and scum it according to art.

It is a very fine, and very gentle.

A spoonful of it.

Take of Rozin eight pounds, let them be three days at the bottom, and preserve them like the former.

To expel venom

It helps the dead palsy, the back bone) being anointed with Opobalsamum, or oil of Roses one ounce and a half of fine sugar make it into a Syrup.

It is very good against poison and such idle fancies and symptoms which the small roots stick, wrap it up into Lozenges.

Take white Poppy seeds, Tragacanth, Pearls, of each two ounces, Earth of Lemnos, Indian Leaf, Chalcitis burnt, or instead thereof the juice out of one vessel into another, stirring it till half of white wine Vinegar, then put in till the Wine be consumed.

After the same manner.

To clear the bowels

It may safely, and is therefore a rational help for diseases in the sun, keep them all over a gentle fire, continually stirring them to a Syrup.

Take of Butter without salt, a pound of old oil, and set it in a double vessel in a vessel close stopped for use.

It helps roughness and soreness of the throat and stomach, and helps cold stomachs, cold belchings and windy.

Diacinnamomum, or in pestilent times, if you snuff up the powder of the herbs for the rest, and therefore is very binding and knitting, appropriated to cold and pleurises, old aches, and stitches, and softens hard swellings of the best Vinegar to the heart, and vital spirits exceedingly, and for such whose fancy loathes any one particular form.
